<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Wentzel, Willard Ferdinand. Journal Kept at Slave Lake, 1802. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0013</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p class="head">August Cont<sup>d</sup> 1802</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">I am not determined as yet whether I shall Keep Adam at <span class="AddHand-editors">[t]</span>he Fort or not<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  But my real opinion is that he is the best man Here &amp; the most fit to Keep at the Point watching the Potties Motions &amp; at the Same time those of the Indians &#8211; &amp; another thing he is the most proper person to send with the <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Grand Coquin</span> &amp; <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Trois Pouce</span> if they should make their appearance<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Wednesday 25<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In the morning 2 of Tluardan's Sons with 2 more Chepeweans arrived &#8211; paid 27 Skins Meat &amp; traded 4 in beaver<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  About an hour after arrived the <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Petit Rat</span> from the <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Grand River</span> the Red Knife Chief he is quite alone with his two women &amp; intends to go to his lands<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  News: are to <span class="AddHand-author">the</span> following purport &#8211; He could not agree with his <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Relations</span> which caused the breach to be so great as to extend from the one S<span class="AddHand-author">ide</span> of the Slave Lake to the other &#8211; also that there are a great band of Red Knifes &amp; Montagnier in the <span style="text-decoration:underline;">River au Foin</span> a Hunting Beaver but he cannot assure us whether they will go to the Red Knife Fort or not<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Tluardan</span> is to Hunt in the Slave River consequently a man will be necassary there<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In the Morning one of the young men Shot an <span style="text-decoration:underline;"><span class="AddHand-editors">[Or]</span>ignal</span> at a very little Distance from this<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Gave <span class="AddHand-editors">[the]</span> Above Chief a Dram &amp; 1 foot Tobaco<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[Too]</span>k 5 pieces Fish in the nets<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  <span class="AddHand-editors">[F]</span>ine weather<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Thursday 26<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Early in the morning Sent <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Adam</span> &amp; <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Tourcotte</span> for the Orignal that was killed yesterday<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In the afternoon they return'd with the two thighs, two <span class="DelHand-author">S</span> Shoulders, two Plat Cotês, <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Brochette</span>, rump, the Fat of Ditto &amp; Heart &#8211; value 9 Skins<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  10 P<sup>s</sup> Fish<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Friday 27<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Gave out Credits &amp; Sent off the Indians &#8211; except the <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Petit Rat</span> &amp; Vieux D'Lisle<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent the Corn de Carribou &amp; Tluardan 10 Skins in Sundry Articles to be divided among them &#8211; as M<sup>r</sup> Thomson recommended those two indians in particular to me<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Gave the Petit Rat the value of 10 Skins in trifles to keep him from going to his Lands<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  He has 10 Skins of Beaver which he will make himself a Robe of<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Either Payment &amp; entreaties could not get them from him &#8211; but he asked me to mark them which I heartily did thus NW on two of the largest <span class="DelHand-author">Dressed</span> tha<span class="AddHand-editors">[t]</span> was</p>

<p align="page-number"><span class="AddHand-editors">[2]</span></p>

